{"TopicId":194384,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How to use RCS as main engine?","CreatedByName":"Pawelk198604","CreatedById":35539,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-02T13:52:22Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Pawelk198604","CreatedById":35539,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-02T13:52:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did not play the game for long time so i forgot some stuff \u003Cspan\u003E:-)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo make long story short i wonder how make my \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E to be used as main engine, because using second stage during rendezvous is terrible inconvenient?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes MechJeb would utilize \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E as main propulsion?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-02T13:55:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/35539-pawelk198604/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002235539\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/35539-pawelk198604/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Pawelk198604\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0IIRC you can right click on your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters and turn on \u0027Fore by Throttle\u0027. I believe you could set it to an action group so that you don\u0027t have your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters firing constantly during launch, for example.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pawelk198604","CreatedById":35539,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-02T14:01:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223795643\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022194384\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221591106123\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183830\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RealKerbal3x\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, RealKerbal3x said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/35539-pawelk198604/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002235539\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/35539-pawelk198604/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Pawelk198604\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0IIRC you can right click on your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters and turn on \u0027Fore by Throttle\u0027. I believe you could set it to an action group so that you don\u0027t have your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters firing constantly during launch, for example.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder how much \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003Edv\u003C/abbr\u003E would be need if use second stage to rise\u00A0perigee just little above ground to make it hit Earth oh i mean Kerbin off course while apogee is 250 km?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndoes it would be just enough to rise\u00A0\u00A0perigee to make orbit circular, the spacecraft have separatron as retro.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Laie","CreatedById":110461,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-02T15:26:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223795642\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022194384\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221591105942\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002235539\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pawelk198604\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Pawelk198604 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes MechJeb would utilize \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E as main propulsion?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes. If \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E is active and no other engine is available, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Mechjeb (mod)\u0022\u003EMJ\u003C/abbr\u003E automatically uses \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E -- I think. Maybe you have to turn that on somewhere, but I think \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Mechjeb (mod)\u0022\u003EMJ\u003C/abbr\u003E does it by default.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOtherwise, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E has a \u0022Forward on Throttle\u0022 Setting in the Advanced Tweakables.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs for delta-V, a standard Mk1 command pod \u002B heatshield \u002B parachute comes to what, 1100kg? It also holds 40kg of monoprop, at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Specific Impulse (rocketry) or Internet Service Provider\u0022\u003EISP\u003C/abbr\u003E=240s that would be enough for 80m/s or so, without even adding a monoprop tank.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow much you can do on 80m/s is up to you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-03T00:41:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMoved to Gameplay Q\u0027s\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}